  "name": "Acts 10:34–48",
  "localizedName": "Acts 10:34–48",
  "content": [
    {
      "tiptap": {
        "type": "doc",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Peter spoke about Jesus’ work and how Jesus freed people from the power of the "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108216",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "devil"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ". He told Cornelius’ family and friends about Jesus’ death and how Jesus rose from the dead."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "He explained that Jesus will bring God’s "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108233",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "judgement"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " to all people. This was the first time that Peter had told Gentiles about Jesus. It was a very important moment."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "As Peter preached, the Holy Spirit came on both the Jews and the Gentiles. This showed that all people are welcome in God’s family. The good news is for everyone no matter what family or group they come from."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Peter and the other Jewish "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108077",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "believers"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " were amazed that God gave his Spirit to Gentiles. Then the new Gentile believers were baptised."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
